<item>
            <title>[LU-17426] parallel cross-directory rename of regular files on single MDT</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17426</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to allow cross-directory rename of regular files (strictly, any non-directory) on the same MDT without holding the BigFilesystemLock (BFL), as file renames cannot change the directory hierarchy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That should improve the performance for these rename operations, and reduce contention between local MDT file renames in different parts of the directory tree.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That would leave directory and cross-MDT renames needing the BFL, which should be an increasingly small fraction of all rename operations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
